Steps to install PostgreSQL on linux Ubuntu 18.04.6 LTS :->

1. Open the terminal in your linux machine.
2. Visit the official website of postgreSQL.
3. If you are unable to find the website, then visit
    https://www.postgresql.org/download/
4. Select Operating System as Linux and Linux Distribution as Ubuntu.
5. Then you will redirect to PostgreSQL apt repository page.
6. Now, you will see the apt repository commands or follow these commands in your terminal:
    a) sudo sh -c 'echo "deb https://apt.postgresql.org/pub/repos/apt $(lsb_release -cs)-pgdg main" > /etc/apt/sources.list.d/pgdg.list'
    b) wget --quiet -O - https://www.postgresql.org/media/keys/ACCC4CF8.asc | sudo apt-key add -
    c) sudo apt-get update
    d) sudo apt-get -y install postgresql
7. Finally, your postgreSQL will have installed in your system.
8. To start , type : 
                sudo -i -u postgres
9. Fill your password it will move into postgres.
10. Then type, psql.
11. It will show you command line interface for postgreSQL.
12. Hurrah! installation has beeen successfully completed.